      { id:'rq-egs-127', label:'Track content variant origins', fulfilled:false, text:'Track content variant origins — which variants came from which canonical article (EGS-127) — IN PROGRESS (2026-04-08). Epic with 4 subtasks; Marcelo Freitas assigned. Susannah\'s #1 analytics priority: one editor (Sarah) manually tracking 700+ stories/month — this automates it. Saner Keles located it in the backlog during 2026-04-08 standup and shared with Susannah. Distinct from PGS-140 (duplicate content pass/fail analytics) and PGS-80 (user event tracking). Replaces PGS-40 (WON\'T DO).' },
      { id:'rq-cluster-map', label:'Map content clusters with Chris and Sara Vallone', fulfilled:false, text:'Map content clusters with Chris and Sara Vallone — document topic areas, hub articles, and spoke articles, then share with Susannah and Kat. Prerequisite for rq-backlinking.' },
      { id:'rq-backlinking', label:'Backlinking / internal source injection', fulfilled:false, text:'Backlinking / internal source injection — surface relevant past McClatchy articles automatically when importing a draft. Valuable for vertical writers building topic clusters. Confirmed buildable by Susannah and Kat.' },
      { id:'rq-cluster-tracking', label:'Automated cluster performance tracking', fulfilled:false, text:'Automated cluster performance tracking — writers manually enter published URLs post-publish and query Marfeel or Amplitude per URL individually. At 10–12 clusters/day this is unsustainable. Goal: harvest published URLs automatically and query performance data for a cluster-level view (parent + all variants). Prerequisite: session with Sara Vallone to understand current manual process before scoping.' },
      { id:'rq-duplicate-content-internal', label:'CSA internal duplicate content check + auto-regeneration (PGS-139)', fulfilled:false, text:'CSA internal duplicate content check + auto-regeneration (PGS-139) — SELECTED FOR DEV. Susannah\'s \'this week/next\' priority. Ideal workflow: CSA runs duplicate check internally first. If variants fail, it regenerates with that feedback to improve quality. If still failing, it notifies the user. Builds on PGS-82 vector embedding similarity scoring. Key concern: UX for extended generation time (Efren Castillo owns UX meeting). Rollout sequence: staging (Mon+) → TEO QA → mitigation strategies → production. @Jim Robinson + @Pierce Williams tagged. Susannah driving coordination.' },
      { id:'rq-duplicate-content-analytics', label:'Duplicate content analytics (PGS-140)', fulfilled:false, text:'Duplicate content analytics (PGS-140) — SELECTED FOR DEV. Susannah\'s \'later this week\' priority. Track: (1) # of times analysis produced pass or fail; (2) identities of failing variant pairs; (3) # of times user clicked reanalyze; (4) # of times CSA auto-regenerated due to internal failure (deferred until PGS-139 ships if not yet live). Goal: surface % of workflows with failures, story types prone to duplication, whether user edits + reanalysis improve outcomes, whether inputs/prompts need changing. @Jim Robinson + @Pierce Williams tagged. Feeds P2 Dashboard Instrumentation via Amplitude once live.' }
