      { id:'rq-search-relevance-spike', label:'Spike: improve search relevance for headline-based and editorial queries (PGS-16', fulfilled:false, text:'Spike: improve search relevance for headline-based and editorial queries (PGS-169) — Priority 1 (Critical), BACKLOG. Current article search returns low-relevance/outdated results when users input full headlines or editorial-style queries. Confirmed failure: pasting \'Everything to Know About Game of Thrones Star Michael Patrick\'s Death: Cause and More\' returned unrelated results; simplified query \'Game of thrones star Michael Patrick death\' also failed. Root causes to investigate: query parsing/normalization for pasted headlines, keyword vs. semantic matching, entity recognition (person/topic/event), recency weighting for news events, internal vs. external content prioritization, current ranking logic limits. Approaches to explore: multi-engine search aggregation (Brave, Tavily, Exa), LLM-based reranking, embedding-based semantic search, hybrid keyword + semantic + recency. Deliverables: root cause analysis, comparison of 2–3 approaches with pros/cons/cost/complexity, implementation recommendation, example improved results.' }
